Allow CMake to find system libgomp when PyTorch doesn't bundle one.

::gentoo's sci-ml/pytorch is built against the system gcc and uses the
system libgomp via gcc's own /usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/$ver/
runtime directory, not via a torch.libs/-style bundle. The upstream
vllm_prepare_torch_gomp_shim() helper probes torch.libs/ + torch/lib/
for libgomp*.so* and returns empty when it doesn't find one;
find_library(... NO_DEFAULT_PATH REQUIRED) then dies because the only
search path it had was empty.

Drop NO_DEFAULT_PATH and add the standard gcc-runtime locations as
explicit HINTS so CMake can find /usr/lib/gcc/.../libgomp.so even when
the shim dir is empty. PyPI-wheel pytorch installations still hit the
shim dir first since PATHS is searched before HINTS.

--- a/cmake/cpu_extension.cmake
+++ b/cmake/cpu_extension.cmake
@@ -32,8 +32,12 @@ else()
     find_library(OPEN_MP
         NAMES gomp
         PATHS ${VLLM_TORCH_GOMP_SHIM_DIR}
-        NO_DEFAULT_PATH
+        HINTS
+            /usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/16
+            /usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/15
+            /usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/14
+            /usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/13
         REQUIRED
     )
     # Set LD_LIBRARY_PATH to include the shim dir at build time to use the same libgomp as PyTorch
     if (OPEN_MP)
